        (139635962, 79186968, 'question', 'Not what you asked, do not store your dates and times as strings in your objects. And don‚Äôt use Date and SimpleDateFormat at all since they were troublesome and are long outdated. Use java.time, the modern Java date and time API. From your format it seems that you would want LocalDateTime for your date and time, though I wonder that depending in circumstances and requirements ZonedDateTime or Instant may be a still better choice. Either implements Comparable.', '2024-11-14 12:56:38', 1, 5772882),
